From 85ffb75ea63efcc67cf959f6003cbb0961e29b52 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vasu Bhatia <git@vbh.ai>
Date: Thu, 30 Apr 2026 14:32:20 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] eink: drive new-pipeline battery colours to pure B/W
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The new unified status-bar battery rendering path
(NewStatusBarIcons / BatteryColors) hardcodes Material colour
constants in Kotlin — Color.parseColor("#34A853") for charging,
"#FBBC04" for battery-saver, "#EA4335" for low battery, plus
GM Gray 500/600 for the meter level. None are reachable from
RRO; framework-res system_* token flips do not apply here.

Drive every fill variant in LightThemeColors / DarkThemeColors
to pure black/white. State that AOSP communicates via colour
is communicated on E-Ink by:

  - the lightning-bolt accessory drawable (charging)
  - the level-bar height itself (low battery)
  - the system notification path (battery-saver, critical)

EPD has no useful colour reproduction and ages unevenly with
sustained green/yellow/red pixels — a coloured battery icon
both reads as muddy and burns into the panel over time. The
legacy ThemedBatteryDrawable colour-levels path is already
neutral after Stage 0 (?android:attr/colorError now resolves
to #000 via the system_error_light override).

Change-Id: I44fd33ad308bec0dd6f02c3e50ea990783992db1
---
 .../battery/unified/BatteryDrawableState.kt   | 66 ++++++++++---------
 1 file changed, 36 insertions(+), 30 deletions(-)

diff --git a/packages/SystemUI/src/com/android/systemui/battery/unified/BatteryDrawableState.kt b/packages/SystemUI/src/com/android/systemui/battery/unified/BatteryDrawableState.kt
index 9f594feb03ab..f9559043929b 100644
--- a/packages/SystemUI/src/com/android/systemui/battery/unified/BatteryDrawableState.kt
+++ b/packages/SystemUI/src/com/android/systemui/battery/unified/BatteryDrawableState.kt
@@ -102,42 +102,48 @@ sealed interface BatteryColors {
     /** Error colors are used for low battery states typically */
     val errorFill: Int
 
-    /** Color scheme appropriate for light mode (dark icons) */
+    /** Color scheme appropriate for light mode (dark icons).
+     *
+     * E-Ink: pure B/W. The frame stroke is opaque black, the unfilled meter
+     * background is opaque white (matches the white status bar so the empty
+     * portion reads as a clean cutout above the level bar), and every fill
+     * variant — normal, charging, battery-saver, low-battery — is the same
+     * solid black. State that AOSP communicates via colour (green=charging,
+     * yellow=battery-saver, red=low-battery) is communicated on E-Ink by:
+     *   - the separate lightning-bolt accessory drawable (charging),
+     *   - the level-bar height itself (low battery),
+     *   - and the system notification path (battery-saver / critical).
+     * EPD has no useful colour reproduction and ages unevenly with sustained
+     * green/yellow/red pixels, so colour-coded battery state would both look
+     * muddy and burn into the panel over time. */
     data object LightThemeColors : BatteryColors {
         override val fg = Color.BLACK
-        // 22% alpha white
-        override val bg: Int = Color.valueOf(1f, 1f, 1f, 0.22f).toArgb()
-
-        // GM Gray 500
-        override val fill = Color.parseColor("#9AA0A6")
-        // GM Gray 600
-        override val fillOnly = Color.parseColor("#80868B")
-
-        // GM Green 500
-        override val activeFill = Color.parseColor("#34A853")
-        // GM Yellow 500
-        override val warnFill = Color.parseColor("#FBBC04")
-        // GM Red 500
-        override val errorFill = Color.parseColor("#EA4335")
+        override val bg: Int = Color.WHITE
+
+        override val fill = Color.BLACK
+        override val fillOnly = Color.BLACK
+
+        override val activeFill = Color.BLACK
+        override val warnFill = Color.BLACK
+        override val errorFill = Color.BLACK
     }
 
-    /** Color scheme appropriate for dark mode (light icons) */
+    /** Color scheme appropriate for dark mode (light icons).
+     *
+     * E-Ink: device should never run in dark mode (white-on-black causes
+     * heavy ghosting on EPD), but kept as a B/W mirror of the light scheme
+     * for safety in case dark mode is toggled. Same rationale as
+     * [LightThemeColors] above. */
     data object DarkThemeColors : BatteryColors {
         override val fg = Color.WHITE
-        // 18% alpha black
-        override val bg: Int = Color.valueOf(0f, 0f, 0f, 0.18f).toArgb()
-
-        // GM Gray 700
-        override val fill = Color.parseColor("#5F6368")
-        // GM Gray 400
-        override val fillOnly = Color.parseColor("#BDC1C6")
-
-        // GM Green 700
-        override val activeFill = Color.parseColor("#188038")
-        // GM Yellow 700
-        override val warnFill = Color.parseColor("#F29900")
-        // GM Red 700
-        override val errorFill = Color.parseColor("#C5221F")
+        override val bg: Int = Color.BLACK
+
+        override val fill = Color.WHITE
+        override val fillOnly = Color.WHITE
+
+        override val activeFill = Color.WHITE
+        override val warnFill = Color.WHITE
+        override val errorFill = Color.WHITE
     }
 
     companion object {
